\section{Marginal distributions}\label{sec:marg}
\subsection{Background}
The lifetime of a newborn {{shall be modelled by}} a positive continuous random variable, say $X$ with distribution function (df) $F$ and survival function {{$S$}}. 
The symbol $\left( x\right)$ will be used to denote a live aged $x$ and $T\left( x\right)={{ (X- x) \lvert X> x}}$ is the remaining lifetime of $\left( x\right)$. The actuarial symbols $_tp_x$ and $_tq_x$ are, respectively, the survival function and the df of $T\left( x\right) $.
 \COM{
